  "text": "Surprisingly, rrp-3, which encodes one of the three RNAdependent RNA polymerases in Neurospora (2), is the most highly induced DRAG (ϳ30-fold induction) in this group of genes. This result suggests that RRP-3, a homolog of QDE-1, may play a role in the formation of viral and retrotransposon dsRNA [CITATION_1] .",
